text.section:
"Individual with disability owned business" means a business:
that is organized under the laws of the United States or the State;
that is majority owned by an individual or individuals determined by the Division of Rehabilitation Services in the State Department of Education to have a disability, as defined by Title 21, Subtitle 3 of the Education Article;
whose majority owner or owners are directly and significantly engaged in the daily operation of the business;
whose workforce includes individuals with disabilities comprising a percentage of the workforce that is at or above the minimum required under the policies or guidelines established by the Pricing and Selection Committee for the Employment Works Program;
whose total gross revenues for contracts assigned under the Program at the time of assignment do not exceed the maximum allowed under policies or guidelines established by the Pricing and Selection Committee for the Employment Works Program; and
that continues to meet all other eligibility criteria established by the Pricing and Selection Committee for the Employment Works Program.
